==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Umpirage
<hw>Um"pi*rage</hw> <pr>(?; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Umpire</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The office of an umpire; the
power, right, or authority of an umpire to decide.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mild <qex>umpirage</qex> of the federal Union.</q> <rj><qau>E.
Everett.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act of umpiring; arbitrament.</def> <rj><au>Bp.
Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Umpire</ent>⟦br⟧
